      transliteration: 'nehābhikrama-nāśo \'sti pratyavāyo na vidyate\nsvalpam apy asya dharmasya trāyate mahato bhayāt',
      translation: 'In this path, there is no loss of effort, nor is there any adverse result. Even a little practice of this discipline protects one from great fear.',
